\frac{2\cot{x}}{\tan{2}x} = \csc^2x-2\;.
\tan 2x=\frac{2 \tan x}{1-\tan ^2x}
\frac{2\cot x}{\tan 2x}=\frac{1-\tan ^2x}{\tan ^2x}=\frac{1}{\tan ^2x}-1=\frac{cos^2x}{sin^2x}-1=
=\frac{1-sin^2x}{sin^2x}-1= \csc^2x-2
\frac{2 \cot x}{\tan 2x}=\frac{2\cos x}{\sin x} \frac{\cos 2x}{\sin 2x}
\cos 2x=\cos ^2x-\sin ^2x
\sin 2x=2\sin x \cos x
\csc ^2x=\frac{1}{\sin^2x}
\sin^2x+\cos^2x=1
